To commit, type "git commit -am "<commit message>"
The -am will commit added files, as well as modifications

To add a new file to the repo, type "git add /path/to/file"

To remove a file from the repo, type "git rm /path/to/file"

To check status of the repo, type "git status"
This lets you know of any changes in your stuff that you might need to commit

After commiting, to push to the repo, type "git push"

To get other people's changes, type "git pull"
